<html><head>
<title>Duplantier: CHINESE BANDITS -- 4/23/96</title></head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a>
<B>BEHIND THE HEADLINES  </B><BR>
<i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.   <br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
April 23, 1996
</i><br>
<h2>
CHINESE BANDITS
</h2>

<P><blockquote><i>  
The communists in China may have nothing but contempt for the 
democratic values of the West, but that doesn't stop them from lusting 
after the prosperity that only a free society can attain.
</blockquote></i>


<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The communists in China long to get their hands on the wealth of Hong 
Kong and Taiwan. They don't seem to understand how that wealth was 
created, or how quickly it would evaporate under communist control. Nor 
do they realize that China itself could be equally prosperous, if they 
would only allow their people the freedom to enjoy the fruits of their own 
labor.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The communists in China also covet the wealth of the United States. 
Since they're not willing to take the steps necessary to create such wealth 
in their own country, however, they've decided to steal ours. The Chinese 
government is actively pirating products and technology patented, 
copyrighted, and trademarked in America. The Chinese have stolen 
computer programs, pharmaceutical products, agricultural chemicals, 
musical recordings, videos, automotive designs, and other intellectual 
properties created by, and rightfully belonging to, American citizens and 
businesses.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
These works of genius are a tribute to the remarkable potential of our 
free-enterprise system. They are the envy of the world, and a mainstay of 
our economy. They are, of course, available for sale to China. And China 
is certainly welcome to compete fairly with us by creating similar 
products on its own. That would involve hard work, however, and a 
liberalization of the Chinese economy that might prove dangerous for the 
slave masters in Beijing. So, instead, China simply copies American 
products illegally. Chinese factories churn out counterfeit CDs, videos, 
and computer programs by the thousands every day, selling their bootleg 
booty around the world.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
These Chinese bandits are undermining the markets of American 
manufacturers to the tune of $1 billion per year. That's how much their 
piracy of U.S. intellectual property is estimated to cost our economy in 
lost exports. Lost exports mean lost jobs, in this case as many as 20,000. 
Unfortunately, American businessmen anxious to tap into the vast 
Chinese market are playing right into the hands of these conniving 
thieves. The experience of the McDonnell Douglas Corporation is just 
one example of how Chinese communists deceive American businessmen 
in order to steal U.S. technology and equipment. By pretending to be in 
the market for a fleet of passenger planes, the Chinese were able to 
negotiate rock-bottom prices on the items that they really wanted -- U.S. 
equipment that would enable them to augment their military capabilities. 
Once they had that equipment in hand, they canceled the order for planes.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Last year, U.S. negotiators persuaded the Chinese to sign yet another 
agreement promising to put an end to their piracy. Getting them to sign 
was easy. Getting them to honor the agreement is another thing. U.S. 
officials keep threatening to impose trade sanctions, but the Chinese don't 
take them seriously, and go right on stealing.
<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




