<html><head>
<title>Duplantier: MOSHER ON CHINA -- 4/26/96</title></head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a>
<B>BEHIND THE HEADLINES  </B><BR>
<i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.   <br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
April 26, 1996
</i><br>
<h2>
MOSHER ON CHINA
</h2>

<P><blockquote><i>  
It's almost too bizarre to be believed, but reports of fetal cannibalism in 
communist China have been confirmed.
</blockquote></i>


<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The rumors circulated for months, and the decent Americans who heard 
them fervently hoped that they were fabricated. Then, documentation 
appeared, and reputable religious and conservative publications had no 
choice but to file their disturbing news reports. The mainstream media 
have yet to acknowledge the unpleasant reality, but even they will not be 
able to ignore it forever.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
In an interview published in the January issue of the Rutherford Institute's 
monthly journal, the executive director of Human Life International's 
Population Research Institute confirms that aborted fetuses are consumed 
for health purposes in China and blames the communist government in 
Beijing for making this revolting practice possible. With as many as 14 
million abortions performed in China in a single year, "there's an ample 
supply of aborted fetuses," says Steven Mosher. Noting that the Chinese 
government is "an avowedly atheistic one which regards human beings 
only as highly evolved apes," Mosher argues that the utilitarian mindset 
inculcated in the Chinese people by their government is what "gives rise 
to fetal consumption."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Don't say it can't happen here, because it can. American society is also 
infected with utilitarianism, and the symptoms of this morally bankrupt 
philosophy are all around us. Mosher warns that "there's very little going 
on in China that isn't happening to one degree or another in the United 
States." The Chinese perform late-term abortions, and so do we. The 
Chinese forcibly sterilize women of child-bearing age, and the practice of 
tying tubes without asking is not unheard-of in American hospitals. The 
Chinese use "surplus" babies for cruel experiments, and we use fetal 
tissue from "surplus" babies for our own sickening scientific studies.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
"In China," observes Mosher, "the use of ultrasound technology to detect 
defects in the unborn child is very common, and many fetuses are aborted 
for the sole reason that they happen to be female. But in the United States 
it's not illegal to abort children for reasons of gender, and it's quite 
common to abort children because a test has revealed a possible 
chromosomal defect."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
China's war on its own children will eventually spread to its elderly. 
Noting that "the population of China is aging more rapidly than any 
human population in the history of the world," as a direct result of its 
coercive birth control program, Mosher predicts that "China's future will 
involve a massive campaign of euthanasia." In fact, the elderly are 
already being denied medical treatment in Chinese hospitals "on the 
ground that treating them is not cost-effective."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Mosher warns that China's self-consuming culture represents "one 
possible future of the United States." He notes that "there is a certain 
element of the radical environmentalist movement which believes that the 
population of the United States . . . should be reduced by half." If we 
don't make a convincing case for life, they may get their wish.
<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




